  description: "socket.htons/__qualname__/__len__()==5 / htonl/__qualname__/__len__()==5 / ntohs/__qualname__/__len__()==5 / gethostname/__qualname__/__eq__('gethostname')==True — 'htons'/'htonl'/'ntohs' are 5 chars each; gethostname's __qualname__ equals its function name; no prior socket spec checks __qualname__.__len__() for htons/htonl/ntohs or __qualname__.__eq__ for gethostname; first __qualname__ length anchor for byte-order functions and first __qualname__.__eq__ anchor for gethostname"
  kind: python_call_eq
